verses.roman:
sei ācārya-gaṇe mora koṭi namaskāra
acyutānanda-prāya, caitanya--jīvana yāṅhāra

synonyms: sei—those; ācārya-gaṇe—unto the spiritual masters; mora—my; koṭi—millions; namaskāra—obeisances; acyutānanda-prāya—almost as good as Acyutānanda; caitanya—Caitanya Mahāprabhu; jīvana—life; yāṅhāra—whose.
translation: I therefore offer my respectful obeisances millions of times to Acyutānanda's actual followers, whose life and soul was Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu.
